        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 7:55PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 755 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Berry, or 14 miles east of Fayette, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boley Springs, Bankston, The Wye, Berry, Oakman, Corona, Townley,
West Corona, and New Lexington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
central and west central Alabama.</instruction>
